lop mind, body, will and spirit as strong as a sword, soft as a pillow and fluid as water.\n\n- Jeffrey\n|\nWhat's fame, after all? It can be what someone writes on your tombstone.\n\n- Peter\n|\nWe cannot decide to love. We cannot compel anyone to love us. There's no secret recipe, only love itself. And we are at its mercy--there's nothing we can do.\n\n- Nina George, The Little Paris Bookshop\n|\nMan thinks many things. He thinks he is One. He is usually several. Until he becomes One, he cannot have a fair idea of what he is at all.\n\n- Idries Shah, The Way of the Sufi\n|\nTo me, religion is about our dignity, not our depravity.\n\n- Yann\n|\nLife is like an onion; you peel it off one layer at a time, and sometimes you weep.\n\n- Carl\n|\nYou skin is so soft. Smells like…”She had to tilt him to get this other arm free and hated knowing how badly she was hurting him as she did so. “Sheer, unadulterated fear?\n\n- Cherry Adair, Hush\n|\nThe seed of suffering in you may be strong, but don't wait until you have no more suffering before allowing yourself to be happy.\n\n- Thich Nhat Hanh, The Heart of the Buddha's Teaching: Transforming Suffering into Peace, Joy, and Liberation\n|\nI was not sorrowful, but only tiredOf everything that ever I desired.\n\n- Ernest Dowson, The Poems and Prose of Ernest Dowson\n|\nWe do not create life, we create death.\n\n- Marie\n|\nIt matters not how fast light may travel, darkness shall always be there awaiting its arrival.\n\n- Mark\n|\nPeople always fear what they don't understand, Evangeline. History proves that.\n\n- Libba Bray, The Diviners\n|\nWhen I'm writing, I'm waiting to see somebody, and I'm waiting to hear them. It's almost like conjuring spirits out of the air, using your own imaginative instability.\n\n- Charles\n|\nOnce you know your Soul, you are never again subject to give your authority away. You own your truth directly and with certainty.\n\n- Elisa Romeo, Meet Your Soul: A Powerful Guide to Connect with Your Most 